  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>Your magical connection to nature allows you to entice, fool, and misdirect plants and fungi as though they were people.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Spell Focus (enchantment), Knowledge (nature) 6 ranks.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>A verdant spell affects plant creatures (even mindless plant creatures) as if they weren't immune to mind-affecting effects, but it has no effect on other types of creatures. A verdant spell uses up a spell slot 2 levels higher than the spell's actual level. This feat works only on mind-affecting spells.<br/><br/><b>Normal</b><br/>Creatures of the plant type are immune to mind-affecting effects.",
